# .trivyignore
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# List CVE IDs here (one per line) to suppress specific Trivy findings.
#
# Use this ONLY for:
#   1. False positives confirmed by your security team
#   2. Vulnerabilities with no available fix AND accepted risk
#   3. CVEs that do not apply to your usage of the affected package
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN          # suppress by CVE ID
#   # comment lines are ignored
#
# Example (DO NOT uncomment without security team approval):
#   CVE-2023-12345          # false positive — not applicable to our build
#   CVE-2024-99999          # no fix available, accepted risk documented in JIRA-123
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add project-specific suppressions below this line:
